  <Project>
    <Name>Neptuo.Productivity.BuildHistory</Name>
    <Type>vsix</Type>
    <Description>Overview of last builds.</Description>
    <Text Language="Markdown">

Build history measures a length of every build (rebuild and clean). 
In the overview window it shows a configured number of last builds, also in the title there is a total count and total time ellapsed during builds.
It gives you an overview how much time you spend during builds.
      
    </Text>
    <LocalUrl>buildhistory</LocalUrl>
    <ProjectUrl>https://github.com/neptuo/Productivity</ProjectUrl>
    <Licence>Apache License, Version 2.0</Licence>
    <LicenceUrl>http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</LicenceUrl>
    <DocumentationUrl>https://github.com/neptuo/Productivity/releases</DocumentationUrl>
    <VsixGalleryId>Neptuo.ProductivityBuildHistory</VsixGalleryId>
    <Images>
      <Main>~/Content/Images/Projects/build-history.png</Main>
    </Images>

    <Version>
      <Name>v1.1</Name>
      <Description>Visual Studio 2019 support.</Description>
      <Description>Blue bar during build.</Description>
      <Description>Fixed default count of shown builds, no need to set it.</Description>
      <Description>Bar length is now computed from lengths of previous builds.</Description>
    </Version>
    <Version>
      <Name>v1.0</Name>
      <Description>Configurable count of builds to store.</Description>
      <Description>Each build length, result (success or failure) and type (build, rebuild or clean).</Description>
    </Version>
  </Project>
  
  <Project>
    <Name>Neptuo.Productivity.FindInFolder</Name>
    <Type>vsix</Type>
    <Description>Quickly find files in selected folder in Solution Explorer.</Description>
    <Text Language="Markdown">
    
Add context menu item to selected folder, project and solution in Solution Explorer. What it does is that it opens a "Find in Files" dialog where selected folder is filled in "Look in".
When solution node is selected, in "Find in Files" will be selected "Entire Solution".
    
    </Text>
    <LocalUrl>findinfolder</LocalUrl>
    <ProjectUrl>https://github.com/neptuo/Productivity</ProjectUrl>
    <Licence>Apache License, Version 2.0</Licence>
    <LicenceUrl>http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0</LicenceUrl>
    <DocumentationUrl>https://github.com/neptuo/Productivity/releases</DocumentationUrl>
    <VsixGalleryId>Neptuo.NeptuoProductivityFindInFolder</VsixGalleryId>
    <Images>
      <Main>~/Content/Images/Projects/find-in-folder.png</Main>
    </Images>

    <Version>
      <Name>v1.1</Name>
      <Description>Visual Studio 2019 support.</Description>
    </Version>
    <Version>
      <Name>v1.0</Name>
      <Description>Context menu item for folder, project and solution.</Description>
    </Version>
  </Project>

